14/03/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- A hand grenade exploded at the home of Kosovo President Ibrahim Rugova early Friday (12 March).
Malcolm Ashby, a UN police spokesman, said it might have been thrown from a passing vehicle.
Rugova and his family were unharmed, but a security guard suffered slight injuries.
Some damage to the house was also reported.
Police have no suspects.
UNMIK chief Harri Holkeri and Kosovo Prime Minister Bajram Rexhepi issued separate statements condemning the attack.
(Albanian News - 13/03/04;
AFP, Tanjug, AP, A1 TV - 12/03/04)
